verbose_text: The 17-dpi time point was also when differences in Hedgehog and Wnt signaling were first detected, with dorsalized differentiations having lower levels of Hedgehog signaling (lower PTCH1 and higher GAS1 expression) and higher levels of Wnt signaling (higher AXIN2 and TNFRSF19 expression) (XREF_FIG C and XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY A).
